LSI 2017: "Human Detection by Histogram of Oriented Gradients"

Files/Folder Structure:
	+ CMakeLists.txt	cmake
	+ lsi_2017.c		Source main file
	+ png			    main library: main algorithm, read/write png, scale ..
    + others            support 

Compile and Run:
	1. Create "build" directory
	2. Move images and matrix files and auto file to "build" directory
	3. Go to "build" directory
	4. Run "cmake path/to/CMakeList.txt"
	5. Run "make"
	6. Run "./hog -i <file>.png" or "./auto.sh"

Example comple and run in linux:
	sislab$ mkdir -p build/
	sislab$ mv *matrix.txt *.png *.sh build/
    sislab$ cd build/
	sislab$ cmake ../
	sislab$ make
	sislab$ ./hog -i test_scale4.png
	sislab$ ./auto.sh

